| Overdragelse til inddrivelse | Transfer for Collection |
| Dækning | Recovery |

## GDPR Rules (critical — enforce in every outcome contract)

- CPR numbers, CVR numbers, names, addresses, email, phone: stored ONLY in person-registry
- All other services store only `person_id` (UUID) and `org_id` (UUID)
- Cross-service data access: REST API calls only — never direct DB access

## Outcome Contract Format

```markdown
# Outcome Contract: {{petition_title}}

## Petition reference
{{petition_id}} — {{one-sentence description}}

## Acceptance criteria
- AC-1: Given [precondition], when [action], then [observable outcome]
- AC-2: ...

## Out of scope
- <what this petition explicitly does NOT cover>

## Test boundary
- **Primary service:** opendebt-{{service}}
- **Layers touched:** controller, service, repository (or: service only, etc.)
- **External dependencies to mock:** person-registry (UUID only), Keycloak (test realm)
- **Integration required:** yes/no — which Testcontainers needed
```

## Your Work

1. Read the petition markdown:
   ```bash
   cat $(bd show {{petition_id}} --json | jq -r '.metadata.petition_path')
   ```

2. Produce the outcome contract at:
   `petitions/{{petition_id}}/{{petition_id}}-outcome-contract.md`

3. Each acceptance criterion must be:
   - Testable (Given/When/Then form)
   - Bounded (one behaviour per criterion)
   - Free of implementation detail (what, not how)

4. Commit:
   ```bash
   git add petitions/{{petition_id}}/
   git commit -m "docs({{petition_id}}): add outcome contract"
   ```

5. Set metadata:
   ```bash
   bd update {{petition_id}} \
     --set-metadata outcome_contract_path="petitions/{{petition_id}}/{{petition_id}}-outcome-contract.md"
   ```

6. Close your step bead:
   ```bash
   bd close {{issue}} "Outcome contract written"
   ```
